\lim_{n\to\infty}\sum_{k=1}^{n}\dfrac{\sigma{(k)}}{k!}= ?
\sigma(n)
\sigma{(N)}=\sum_{d|N}d
\sum_{n=1}^\infty\frac{\sigma(n)}{n!}=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\frac{(id*1)(n)}{n!}=\sum_{n=1}^\infty n\sum_{k=1}^\infty\frac{1}{(kn)!}=\sum_{n=1}^\infty \sum_{t=1}^n e^{e^{2\pi i t/n}}-1
\sum_{n=1}^\infty\frac{\sigma(n)}{n!}=\sum_{n=1}^\infty \sum_{t=1}^n (\large{e^{e^{2\pi i t/n}}}-1)
